The paper deals with network coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The network considered in the paper is a directed acyclic graph, which is a common structure in networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the performance of linear codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.SI). The use of commutative algebraic techniques is a unique approach to deriving linear network coding results, which could fall under the category of algebraic geometry or algebraic coding theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses fundamental limits of network coding, which could fall under the category of complexity theory (cs.CC).
